AILevel.Name: Advanced
AILevel.Description: The best - all strategies are employed.  This AI should never lose.  It will only win if the opponent makes a mistake, but otherwise, it at least tie.
AILevel.AIStrategyNames: WinIfPossible, PlayInMiddleIfAvailable, Random, PreventWinIfPossible, ForceWinNextTurn, PreventForceWinNextTurn, PlayInCornerIfAvailable, SetupForceWinNextTurn, PreventSetupForceWinNextTurn, LearnFromMistakes

AILevel.Name: Intermediate
AILevel.Description: This guy's pretty good - but not the best
AILevel.AIStrategyNames: WinIfPossible, PlayInMiddleIfAvailable, Random, PreventWinIfPossible, ForceWinNextTurn, PreventForceWinNextTurn

AILevel.Name: Beginner
AILevel.Description: Wins, prevents a win or plays randomly.

CellPattern.Name: TwoInARowTop
CellPattern.Description: Two marks top left, top middle with top right empty - and then a full rotation/flip scheme.

CellPattern.Name: EdgeWin
CellPattern.Description: Starting with the top row, 3 additional rotates will find all edge wins.

CellPattern.Name: TwoOutsideTop
CellPattern.Description: Top left and top right filled, middle empty - finds all positions with 3 rotations.

CellPattern.Name: TwoInARowDiagonal
CellPattern.Description: Two in a row on the diagonal, with the third cell empty - finds all positions with 3 rotations.

CellPattern.Name: TwoOutsideDiagonal
CellPattern.Description: Top left and bottom right with middle empty  - 1 rotation finds the one variation of the starting pattern.

CellPattern.Name: TwoOutsideMiddle
CellPattern.Description: Middle left and right, center empty - 1 rotation finds the one variation of the starting pattern.

CellPattern.Name: MiddleWin
CellPattern.Description: Starting with the middle row selected, a single rotations finds both middle wins

CellPattern.Name: TwoInARowMiddle
CellPattern.Description: Two in a row on the middle row, right side empty - finds all positions with 3 rotations.

AIStrategy.Name: PreventWinIfPossible
AIStrategy.Description: Prevent opponent from using WinIfPossible strategy

AIStrategy.Name: ForceWinNextTurn
AIStrategy.Description: Check for a move that will force a win the next turn, regardless of what the opponent does.

AIStrategy.Name: PreventForceWinNextTurn
AIStrategy.Description: Prevent opponent from using ForceWinNextTurn strategy

AIStrategy.Name: WaitsForInstruction
AIStrategy.Description: Plays as proxy for a human.  A UI is needed to communicate the human's intentions.

AIStrategy.Name: PlayInMiddleIfAvailable
AIStrategy.Description: If there are no other winning strategies, play in the middle cell

AIStrategy.Name: Random
AIStrategy.Description: Choice from a random selection amongst available cells

AIStrategy.Name: LearnFromMistakes
AIStrategy.Description: Plays randomly, but keeps track of what moves are made, and learn from mistakes

AIStrategy.Name: PlayInCornerIfAvailable
AIStrategy.Description: If there are any corner positions available, player there

AIStrategy.Name: PreventSetupForceWinNextTurn
AIStrategy.Description: Prevent opponent from using SetupForceWinNextTurn strategy

AIStrategy.Name: SetupForceWinNextTurn
AIStrategy.Description: Check if there's a move which will allow a force win next turn.

AIStrategy.Name: WinIfPossible
AIStrategy.Description: If any two cells are already filled in by the AI, and the 3rd cell in that row is available, play there.
